&lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1tjzxzBfTitTL7iZ0eBWJOqK_I8A6cqZNDyXvBtQ4y4I/edit"&gt;Troubleshooting Common&amp;nbsp;Errors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Email&amp;nbsp;Options&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Python&amp;nbsp;Anywhere&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Allows use of Gmail &lt;span class="caps"&gt;SMTP&lt;/span&gt; for free users.  They also mention Mailgun and Sendgrid. Note, it is best to set up a new gmail account for this since allowing your account to connect via &lt;span class="caps"&gt;SMTP&lt;/span&gt; is a risk. &lt;a href="https://help.pythonanywhere.com/pages/SMTPForFreeUsers/"&gt;Details&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Heroku&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Typically Heroku does not allow Gmail. They suggest using Sendgrid which has a free account tier. &lt;a href="https://elements.heroku.com/addons/sendgrid"&gt;Details&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Providers&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://sendgrid.com/"&gt;SendGrid&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://mailtrap.io/"&gt;mailtrap&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://www.mailgun.com/"&gt;mailgun&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="Tutorial"></category></entry></feed>